[[File:Nam Kwong Filling Station.JPG|thumb|NKOIL [[filling station]] in Macau]] [[File:Water Treatment Plant.jpg|thumb|[[Water treatment]] plant in Macau]]
'''Energy in Macau''' is related to all of the type of [[energy]] and its related infrastructure used in [[Macau]], [[China]]. Energy-related affairs is administered under the [[Secretariat for Transport and Public Works (Macau)|Secretariat for Transport and Public Works]] of the [[Government of Macau]].
==Natural gas== Macau import its [[natural gas]] supply from [[Hengqin Island]] in [[Zhuhai]], [[Guangdong]]. The pipeline has a capacity of 520 million m<sup>3</sup> of natural gas per year. The sole gas importer in Macau is '''Sinosky Energy (Holdings) Co. Ltd.''' ({{zh|t=中天能源控股有限公司}}).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://macaubusinessdaily.com/Economy/Insufficient-LNG-electricity-year |title=Insufficient LNG for electricity this year |publisher=Macau Business Daily |date= |accessdate=2014-04-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226051359/http://macaubusinessdaily.com/Economy/Insufficient-LNG-electricity-year |archivedate=2013-12-26 |df= }}</ref>
==Petroleum== Petroleum and other petrochemical products in Macau is handled by '''Nam Kwong Petroleum & Chemical Co., Ltd.''' ('''NKOIL'''; {{zh|t=南光石油化工有限公司}}) from its trading, storage, transportation, wholesale and retail, including the installation and maintenance of gas and fuel supply system.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nkoil.net/Member/ColumnList?type=1 |title=南光石油化工有限公司 - 南光石油 |publisher=Nkoil.net |date= |accessdate=2014-04-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131226080616/http://www.nkoil.net/Member/ColumnList?type=1 |archivedate=2013-12-26 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.namkwong.com.mo/en/Subsidiaries/PetroleumandChemical/index.html |title=Nam Kwong Petroleum & Chemical Co., Ltd |publisher=Namkwong.com.mo |date= |accessdate=2014-04-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131225225639/http://www.namkwong.com.mo/en/Subsidiaries/PetroleumandChemical/index.html |archivedate=2013-12-25 |df= }}</ref>
==Water supply== Water supply in Macau is handled by [[Macao Water]].
