{{notability|date=November 2015}}
The '''GEMIX''' is a report commissioned by the [[Belgium|Belgian]] Minister of Climate and Energy, [[Paul Magnette]]. The full title in French is ''Quel mix énergétique idéal pour la Belgique aux horizons 2020 et 2030?''. It was completed on 30 September 2009<ref name=GEMIX>Groupe Gemix, ''[http://economie.fgov.be/fr/binaries/rapport_gemix_2009_fr_tcm326-76356.pdf Quel mix énergétique idéal pour la Belgique aux horizons 2020 et 2030?]''</ref> and published on 9 October 2009. The report received a lot of publicity, due mainly to its recommendations on [[nuclear power]].

It was written by Dominique Woitrin, Marie Pierre Fauconnier, Danielle Devogelaer, Jacques Percebois, Luigi De Paoli, Jacques De Ruyck and Wolfgang Eichhammer. [[Luc Dufresne]] was president of the workgroup.<ref name=GEMIX/>

