{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Geomagnetic latitude''' is a parameter analogous to [[latitude|geographic latitude]], except that, instead of being defined relative to the [[geographic poles]], it is defined by the axis of the [[dipole model of the Earth's magnetic field|geomagnetic dipole]], which can be accurately extracted from the [[International Geomagnetic Reference Model]].   

