[[he:בריטניה הגדולה#נהרות]]

'''M85''' is a fuel blending 85% [[methanol]] and 15% petrol.<ref>{{cite web|title=Methanol (M85)|url=http://www.altfuels.org/backgrnd/altftype/m85.html|accessdate=24 June 2011}}</ref> M85 is a similar blend to the [[E85]] biofuel, however M85 fuel cannot run in vehicles intended to use E85 fuel. While similar, M85 isn't as well known as its [[ethanol]] counterpart. Methanol is considered a viable fuel alternative as it contains high levels of hydrogen.

